00:19:19,417 --> 00:19:24,979
♪Whose softness has decayed?♪

285
00:19:25,321 --> 00:19:28,648
♪Lift the dust, feel it with your soul♪

286
00:19:28,670 --> 00:19:33,586
♪The chains of destiny
have long bound us♪

287
00:19:33,748 --> 00:19:36,584
♪To each other♪

288
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:39,495
♪If you don't die, I won't stop♪

289
00:19:39,897 --> 00:19:42,303
♪Let's witness together♪

290
00:19:42,325 --> 00:19:46,228
♪The end♪

291
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,519
Why are we in the middle of nowhere

292
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:02,559
this late at night?

293
00:20:05,550 --> 00:20:07,940
I can take you out to sing,
dance, and drink. Is that okay?

294
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,240
Sorry, I forgot

295
00:20:12,039 --> 00:20:13,039
you're still injured.

296
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:17,799
Mom,

297
00:20:19,119 --> 00:20:19,960
recently,

298
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:22,519
I don't know how to face Siyuan.

299
00:20:23,660 --> 00:20:25,380
You feel the same way, don't you?

300
00:20:31,599 --> 00:20:32,440
Are you blaming me?

301
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:41,000
They have to separate anyway.

302
00:20:43,279 --> 00:20:44,640
I've been thinking a lot

303
00:20:44,759 --> 00:20:46,440
about my past with Zhibai.

304
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:49,960
I used to believe

305
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,920
that the longer we were apart,

306
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:54,600
the more our memories would fade.

307
00:20:57,519 --> 00:20:59,119
But somehow,

308
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:03,119
they're becoming clearer.

309
00:21:15,599 --> 00:21:16,599
I realized

310
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:20,349
that the hardest part

311
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:21,960
isn't when two people are separated.

312
00:21:24,359 --> 00:21:25,559
It's when the memories

313
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:31,720
keep coming back.

314
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:37,839
It could be

315
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:41,720
a street we once walked together

316
00:21:44,319 --> 00:21:46,359
or the unique scent of him.

317
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,680
They become more and more...

318
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:54,920
Inescapable.

319
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:57,960
Finally,

320
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,079
they turn into a deadly weapon.

321
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,440
I have so many things
I want to tell him.

322
00:22:17,759 --> 00:22:18,720
But it's okay.

323
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:22,960
We'll meet again.

324
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,000
Maybe

325
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:30,640
in another world.

326
00:22:35,079 --> 00:22:37,640
I want to share every single bit

327
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:44,680
that happened

328
00:22:47,279 --> 00:22:48,359
over the past year.

329
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,519
Move.

330
00:24:00,839 --> 00:24:01,960
Stop.

331
00:24:02,119 --> 00:24:03,000
Turn right.

332
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:05,720
Hold on tight.

333
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:20,079
Move.

334
00:24:25,759 --> 00:24:26,640
What's on your mind?

335
00:24:31,359 --> 00:24:33,319
How do you feel now?

336
00:24:38,279 --> 00:24:39,640
To be honest, I must thank you.

337
00:24:43,559 --> 00:24:44,759
If you put it that way,

338
00:24:45,079 --> 00:24:46,359
I should apologize.

339
00:24:47,279 --> 00:24:49,039
I was biased against you.

340
00:24:49,519 --> 00:24:51,200
But after going through
so much together,

341
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,400
I've realized
you have this energy in you.

342
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,359
Do you remember this?

343
00:25:08,060 --> 00:25:09,840
Every time I see these teeth marks,

344
00:25:10,519 --> 00:25:11,880
they remind me of you as a kid.

345
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,559
I used to wonder
what would happen to you

346
00:25:16,599 --> 00:25:17,759
after going through all that

347
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,079
at such a young age.

348
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:21,880
Would your life be ruined?

349
00:25:22,060 --> 00:25:23,740
Was there anything I could do for you?

350
00:25:25,599 --> 00:25:28,000
But in the end, you became a great man.

351
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:30,599
You saved yourself.

352
00:25:34,359 --> 00:25:35,279
Not yet.

353
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,599
Not until I find the truth.

354
00:25:41,820 --> 00:25:43,880
That's the only way
I can truly save myself.

355
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:50,359
I won't give up.

356
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,599
I'll keep searching

357
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:55,039
in my own way.

358
00:26:03,759 --> 00:26:05,720
To be frank, this case is complicated.

359
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:07,960
The deeper I dig,

360
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,000
the more new problems I uncover.

361
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:12,400
I'm short of manpower.

362
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:17,839
You need my help?

363
00:26:20,300 --> 00:26:22,270
Didn't your director want me
to recuse myself?

364
00:26:22,759 --> 00:26:23,559
Yes.

365
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:26,160
Which is why I've been persuading him.

366
00:26:26,799 --> 00:26:27,599
I told him

367
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:29,900
that even if we stopped you
from investigating,

368
00:26:30,119 --> 00:26:31,640
you wouldn't give up so easily.

369
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:33,520
Instead of wasting our energy
to stop you,

370
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:35,160
it's better for us to work together.

371
00:26:37,799 --> 00:26:38,599
What's his response?

372
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:41,839
He thought it made sense.

373
00:26:47,359 --> 00:26:48,160
That's good, though.

374
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:50,590
Everything that happened that night
was unexpected.

375
00:26:52,759 --> 00:26:54,799
Looking back over the past few days,

376
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:57,100
I've noticed a lot of things
that don't add up.

377
00:26:58,839 --> 00:26:59,640
Why did the car

378
00:27:00,599 --> 00:27:01,880
suddenly explode?

379
00:27:02,599 --> 00:27:03,319
Why did the truck

380
00:27:03,319 --> 00:27:05,079
force the car behind it to stop?

381
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:08,720
Who was inside?

382
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:11,030
And who's the fourth person
in that photo...

383
00:27:11,119 --> 00:27:12,079
I'll tell you that.

384
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:13,519
But you see,

385
00:27:13,880 --> 00:27:15,359
I vouched for you this time,

386
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:16,960
so you have to follow my orders.

387
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:19,360
I'll have to take responsibility
if anything goes wrong.

388
00:27:22,039 --> 00:27:22,839
All right.

389
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:31,200
Hello?

390
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:33,720
Got it.

391
00:27:36,119 --> 00:27:37,839
We arrested one of Liu Haixun's men,

392
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:38,759
Meng Kun.

393
00:27:39,180 --> 00:27:40,790
He was severely injured a few days ago

394
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:42,340
and has been in a coma at the hospital.

395
00:27:42,380 --> 00:27:43,220
He's awake now.

396
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:44,680
Let's go check on him.

397
00:27:47,519 --> 00:27:47,920
Let's go.

398
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:05,000
Bai Han and Mr. Xun
had a deal that day,

399
00:28:06,060 --> 00:28:07,560
but Xun requested that Bai Han

400
00:28:08,079 --> 00:28:09,920
bring everyone over.

401
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:12,559
Bai Han agreed.

402
00:28:14,039 --> 00:28:17,440
Later, however, he worried

403
00:28:18,799 --> 00:28:20,240
that if we broke our word

404
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,319
and turned on them,

405
00:28:23,319 --> 00:28:26,640
he and his goods wouldn't be able
to leave the dried fruit factory.

406
00:28:28,240 --> 00:28:30,960
So, he came up with a plan.

407
00:28:31,220 --> 00:28:33,340
That's to set up separate locations
for the deal.

408
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:37,039
When the dealer arrives,
and the goods will be sent out.

409
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:40,839
Then examine the goods and pay up.

410
00:29:01,119 --> 00:29:01,920
What does this mean?

411
00:29:02,359 --> 00:29:03,480
It's our rule.

412
00:29:05,079 --> 00:29:05,920
We'll pat you down.

413
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,720
Is this how you treat your guests?

414
00:29:10,519 --> 00:29:11,319
Bai Han,

415
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:13,480
since you're here,

416
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,840
let's show some respect for each other.

417
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:19,799
Fine.

418
00:29:20,559 --> 00:29:21,640
I'll do you this favor.

419
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:25,680
Come on.

420
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:47,519
You're not very professional.

421
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,359
You should improve yourself.

422
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:19,079
I'm here.

423
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:21,200
Can you deliver the goods now?

424
00:30:22,519 --> 00:30:23,319
Address.

425
00:30:29,580 --> 00:30:32,110
The intersection of Pingluo Expressway
and Bucha Highway.

426
00:30:33,079 --> 00:30:34,720
My men are waiting there.

427
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:10,030
Xun is waiting for you inside there.

428
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:20,400
Where's Liu Haixun?

429
00:31:21,920 --> 00:31:22,839
I'm here.

430
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:26,319
Bai Han, I was worried you'd
point your pun at me again,

431
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:28,519
so I thought a little distance
would be best.

432
00:31:33,079 --> 00:31:33,640
Bai Han,

433
00:31:34,279 --> 00:31:35,640
there's something I've always been

434
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:36,319
curious about.

435
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:38,759
Why do you keep going after Song En?

436
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,240
None of your business.

437
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:42,480
Come on, tell me.

438
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,160
I've already delivered your goods.

439
00:31:44,599 --> 00:31:46,160
We'll be friends from now on.

440
00:31:46,359 --> 00:31:47,559
You don't even dare to show up.

441
00:31:47,559 --> 00:31:49,480
We're not friends.

442
00:31:50,079 --> 00:31:51,640
Don't flatter yourself.

443
00:32:07,559 --> 00:32:08,359
Surprise.

444
00:32:08,759 --> 00:32:09,680
Surprise.

445
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:11,200
Bai Han,

446
00:32:11,559 --> 00:32:12,240
I'm sorry.

447
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:13,960
We don't have a grudge.

448
00:32:14,279 --> 00:32:16,119
Tie Xin put me up to this.

449
00:32:16,260 --> 00:32:17,720
If you turn into a vengeful ghost,

450
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:18,920
please don't come after me.

451
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:19,960
Go after him.

452
00:32:20,039 --> 00:32:20,920
Didn't you say

453
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:23,440
you didn't want to be
Tie Xin's lackey anymore?

454
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:28,480
Being a lackey isn't so bad.

455
00:32:28,839 --> 00:32:30,720
Sometimes, you get beaten and scolded,

456
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:32,960
but you never go hungry.

457
00:32:34,279 --> 00:32:35,079
Bai Han,

458
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,400
you didn't answer my question,

459
00:32:38,119 --> 00:32:40,240
but I can offer you a secret.

460
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:43,720
I was part

461
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:45,640
of that fire as well.

462
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:47,000
In fact,

463
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:50,079
I should be on your hit list.

464
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,240
Liu Haixun,

465
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:55,240
you deserve to die.

466
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:58,720
Sadly, you don't get to decide that.

467
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:00,359
Bai Han,

468
00:33:01,039 --> 00:33:01,839
do you know why

469
00:33:01,839 --> 00:33:03,720
I targeted you guys back then?

470
00:33:04,039 --> 00:33:05,920
It wasn't just about pleasing Gai De.

471
00:33:06,519 --> 00:33:07,279
You young ones

472
00:33:07,279 --> 00:33:09,240
were too naive and brazen

473
00:33:10,079 --> 00:33:12,039
to pursue the so-called justice.

474
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:14,759
I wanted to teach you a lesson

475
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:17,319
and show you what darkness really is.

476
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:21,119
Stop wasting your effort.

477
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:23,519
The entire space is bulletproof.

478
00:33:23,519 --> 00:33:25,279
You can't get out.

479
00:33:26,839 --> 00:33:27,680
Liu Haixun,

480
00:33:29,359 --> 00:33:30,599
you'll go to hell.

481
00:33:31,279 --> 00:33:33,119
I'm not going to hell.

482
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:36,900
I'll give that chance to whoever wants it.

483
00:33:37,880 --> 00:33:39,279
Take this. You do it.

484
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:40,640
It's not good to kill.

485
00:33:40,759 --> 00:33:41,799
Take it.

486
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:06,440
Press the button.

487
00:34:10,719 --> 00:34:13,260
Are you saying that the explosion
at the dried fruit factory

488
00:34:13,260 --> 00:34:15,440
was planned by Liu Haixun
to kill Bai Han?

489
00:34:15,559 --> 00:34:16,639
Is Bai Han dead?

490
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:18,280
The factory didn't explode.

491
00:34:18,460 --> 00:34:20,960
We didn't find Bai Han's body
in the factory.

492
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:23,239
They never even entered.

493
00:34:23,719 --> 00:34:24,519
Right?

494
00:34:27,559 --> 00:34:28,360
Yes.

495
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:31,800
The two newcomers

496
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:35,000
were Bai Han's spies.

497
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:38,639
Help me.

498
00:34:41,079 --> 00:34:41,960
Help me.

499
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,039
They set up a room

500
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:08,400
inside a refrigerated truck

501
00:35:09,039 --> 00:35:10,039
that looked exactly

502
00:35:10,039 --> 00:35:11,280
like Xun's office.

503
00:35:12,199 --> 00:35:15,440
Then, they planted someone there

504
00:35:16,400 --> 00:35:17,559
to move the camera

505
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:20,679
to the refrigerated truck.

506
00:35:23,960 --> 00:35:25,480
After I left that day,

507
00:35:26,679 --> 00:35:28,519
they knocked everyone else out.

508
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:45,800
Then, they got into
the refrigerated truck they prepared

509
00:35:46,679 --> 00:35:47,880
and followed behind us.

510
00:35:48,039 --> 00:35:48,840
Hold on.

511
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,280
You mentioned

512
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:53,159
the person who ordered Liu Haixun
to kill Bai Han was Tie Xin?

513
00:35:56,039 --> 00:35:56,760
Right.

514
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:57,960
Who is this person?

515
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:02,800
I don't know.

516
00:36:04,039 --> 00:36:05,480
All I know is he's a big shot.

517
00:36:06,159 --> 00:36:07,679
Even Xun listens to him.

518
00:36:08,280 --> 00:36:09,440
Who was the other guy

519
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:10,719
with Bai Han?

520
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:17,519
He was about my height.

521
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:19,639
Double eyelids.

522
00:36:21,159 --> 00:36:22,400
High nose bridge.

523
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:24,800
He had...

524
00:36:26,880 --> 00:36:28,679
a Cantonese accent. Right.

525
00:36:29,559 --> 00:36:30,559
A Cantonese accent.

526
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:32,709
Chief,

527
00:36:32,710 --> 00:36:34,960
this is the surveillance footage
from the crime scene.

528
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:03,679
He was outfoxed.

529
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:05,039
He never expected

530
00:37:05,039 --> 00:37:07,760
to fall into the very scheme he designed.

531
00:37:12,199 --> 00:37:13,039
What's on your mind?

532
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:18,679
I'm thinking about

533
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,960
the people in the footage.

534
00:37:21,639 --> 00:37:22,880
The fat guy is Gan,

535
00:37:23,580 --> 00:37:24,900
and the skinny one is Tai.

536
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:27,100
Both of them worked under Bai Han.

537
00:37:28,039 --> 00:37:29,239
Who's the other one?

538
00:37:31,660 --> 00:37:34,360
He's wearing a hat the whole time.
I couldn't see his face.

539
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:35,880
He's with Bai Han, for sure.

540
00:37:36,039 --> 00:37:37,679
We'll get him when we catch Bai Han.

541
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:40,639
Why?

542
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:42,440
Who do you think he is?

543
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:48,199
No idea.

544
00:37:53,732 --> 00:37:56,910
(Monitoring Room)

545
00:38:11,740 --> 00:38:12,840
Have you found anything?

546
00:38:15,540 --> 00:38:18,360
I need surveillance data for
the whole city for the past seven days.

547
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:19,960
As many as you can get.

548
00:38:21,599 --> 00:38:22,519
The whole city?

549
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:25,519
Are you trying to find one person

550
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:26,960
among 700,000 people?

551
00:38:27,119 --> 00:38:27,760
Yes.

552
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:32,239
All right.

553
00:39:26,852 --> 00:39:32,050
(Elderly Care Center, Buhe City)

554
00:39:47,641 --> 00:39:52,079
♪The night stretches long,
like an endless hallway♪

555
00:39:53,441 --> 00:39:58,598
♪Without moonlight
or a god to guide the way♪

556
00:39:59,235 --> 00:40:04,106
♪Memories drip
within the center of my heart♪

557
00:40:04,361 --> 00:40:09,125
♪Burning you away,
leaving only emptiness♪

558
00:40:09,332 --> 00:40:12,144
♪The distorted truth♪

559
00:40:12,322 --> 00:40:17,907
♪Is tampered with,
buried, and forgotten♪

560
00:40:20,556 --> 00:40:26,470
♪Beyond the embers,
the wound remains warm♪

561
00:40:26,636 --> 00:40:31,421
♪It lights up again♪

562
00:40:32,150 --> 00:40:37,783
♪Whose hands♪

563
00:40:38,038 --> 00:40:41,362
♪Are pulling the strings?♪

564
00:40:41,519 --> 00:40:43,946
♪Who stands at the end of the lie?♪

565
00:40:43,955 --> 00:40:49,436
♪Behind the mask♪

566
